full_requirement_text: All trial records must comply with ALCOA principles.
original_text:
Data Integrity & Record Management
Section 6: Data Integrity
1. All trial records must comply with ALCOA principles.
2. Electronic records must have audit trails and access control.
3. Records must be retained as per regulatory requirements.

Training & Documentation Control
Section 5: Training
1. All trial personnel must receive role-specific GCP training prior to trial activities.
2. Training must be documented and retained.
3. Training effectiveness must be periodically assessed.

full_requirement_text: The Investigator must conduct the trial in compliance with the approved protocol.
original_text:
Protocol Compliance & Deviations
Section 4: Protocol Compliance
1. The Investigator must conduct the trial in compliance with the approved protocol.
2. The Investigator must not deviate from the protocol without sponsor approval.
3. All protocol deviations must receive prior IRB/IEC approval, unless required to eliminate
immediate hazard.

full_requirement_text: All Serious Adverse Events (SAEs) must be reported immediately to the sponsor.
original_text:
GCP – Safety Reporting Requirements
Section 3: Serious Adverse Events (SAEs)
1. All Serious Adverse Events (SAEs) must be reported immediately to the sponsor.
2. Initial SAE reports must be followed by detailed written follow-up reports.
3. All protocol-defined critical adverse events must be reported, even if non-serious.

full_requirement_text: The Investigator must be qualified by education to conduct the clinical trial.
original_text:
Good Clinical Practice (GCP) – Investigator Responsibilities
Section 1: Investigator Qualification
1. The Investigator must be qualified by education, training, and experience to conduct the clinical
trial.
2. The Investigator must maintain documentation demonstrating qualification.
Section 2: Delegation of Duties
3. The Investigator must maintain a delegation log.
4. The Investigator must ensure delegated personnel are appropriately qualified and trained.
